cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the application of deep learning and active inference for autonomous robot navigation, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning to learn state representations from high-dimensional sensory data such as camera frames suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the use of generative models and Bayesian inference suggests a potential connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
